{"TopicId":179961,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.3.1-1.5.1] SunFixer 1.0.1 [obsolete]","CreatedByName":"taniwha","CreatedById":57176,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-21T03:25:12Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"taniwha","CreatedById":57176,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-21T03:25:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP 1.3.0 \u0022fixed\u0022 vessel shadows on the ground by \u0022breaking\u0022 the position of the sun in the sky (as a workaround for a Unity bug). 1.3.1 fixed the sun\u0027s position but the shadows it cast were still highly granular in their motion. KSP 1.4.0 brought a new version of Unity which fixed the bug 1.3 worked around, but the workaround remains in effect in KSP, thus the shadows continue to jerk across the terrain.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis tiny mod (seriously: other than some setup and sanity checking code, it\u0027s one line) mitigates the workaround, bringing back shadows that move smoothly with the position of the sun in the sky.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003EDownload: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://taniwha.org/~bill/SunFixer_v1.0.1.zip\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESunFixer 1.0.1\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003ELicense: GPLv3\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003ESource: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/taniwha/SunFixer\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Egithub\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is no configuration or tuning.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe release was compiled for 1.5.1, but my testing included using a version for 1.4.x in 1.5.1, and the mod is so simple it\u0027s difficult to break, so it should work on any KSP that needs it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr was so simple: now with support for Kopernicus (thanks to \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113164-thomas-p/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022113164\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113164-thomas-p/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Thomas P.\u003C/a\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMany thanks to \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/73725-5thhorseman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002273725\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/73725-5thhorseman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@5thHorseman\u003C/a\u003E for a video showing off SunFixer:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/HAvox3_zFfw?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-01-24T10:44:40Z\u0022 title=\u002201/24/2019 10:44  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 24, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by taniwha\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-21T05:17:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57176-taniwha/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257176\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57176-taniwha/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@taniwha\u003C/a\u003E!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"theJesuit","CreatedById":122369,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-21T08:09:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57176-taniwha/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257176\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57176-taniwha/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@taniwha\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy god... it\u0027s full of shadows!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeriously... with ALL the suggestions or which mods should be stock, surely you have to agree \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266485\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SQUAD\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0that this is the one!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPeace.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"avalancha","CreatedById":143355,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-21T09:47:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou wouldn\u0027t have by any chance a video comparison before and after the mod? Because for me in 1.5.1 the shadows are... Fine?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"woeller","CreatedById":174556,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-21T17:11:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223491236\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179961\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542793655\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022143355\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022avalancha\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, avalancha said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou wouldn\u0027t have by any chance a video comparison before and after the mod? Because for me in 1.5.1 the shadows are... Fine?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe shadows are fine. The shadow movement isn\u0027t. This mod will fix it. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-21T18:05:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll try to make a quick video. If I\u0027m super up for it I\u0027ll try to make it a gif.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut that won\u0027t be until tomorrow.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"taniwha","CreatedById":57176,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-21T23:58:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have released version 1.0.1 of SunCatcher. Many thanks to \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113164-thomas-p/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022113164\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113164-thomas-p/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Thomas P.\u003C/a\u003E for the Kopernicus patch: all suns get the tweak.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-22T02:14:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223491473\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179961\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542823549\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll try to make a quick video. If I\u0027m super up for it I\u0027ll try to make it a gif.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut that won\u0027t be until tomorrow.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually I may need more of an explanation of what this does, because I just did a close (like less than 100 meters at orbital velocity) Minmus flyby and the shadow looked exactly the same with and without the mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: OH it\u0027s the sun moving, not the ship. Okay yeah I see that. I thought this fixed how your shadow vanished on descent or something like that \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Nope, still not seeing it. I reinstate my request. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-11-22T02:26:16Z\u0022 title=\u002211/22/2018 02:26  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 22, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by 5thHorseman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vardicd","CreatedById":75832,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-22T02:54:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223491690\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179961\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542852843\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n41 minutes ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually I may need more of an explanation of what this does, because I just did a close (like less than 100 meters at orbital velocity) Minmus flyby and the shadow looked exactly the same with and without the mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: OH it\u0027s the sun moving, not the ship. Okay yeah I see that. I thought this fixed how your shadow vanished on descent or something like that \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe this has more to do with the jerkiness of shadows moving across the ground, due to the movement of the sun in the sky. if you watch the shadows of the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E moving across the ground as the day passes in a relatively low time warp, then install this mod and watch again, you should see a big difference. See below, though I\u0027m sure you can do a much better job showing it:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/LlhNe59KEKk?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-11-22T02:55:18Z\u0022 title=\u002211/22/2018 02:55  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 22, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by vardicd\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"taniwha","CreatedById":57176,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-22T03:02:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223491710\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179961\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542855279\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002275832\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022vardicd\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, vardicd said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe this has more to do with the jerkiness of shadows moving across the ground, due to the movement of the sun in the sky. if you watch the shadows of the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E moving across the ground as the day passes in a relatively low time warp, then install this mod and watch again, you should see a big difference. See below, though I\u0027m sure you can do a much better job showing it:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, this is the issue that SunFixer fixes. The issue that KSP 1.3 fixed is the ship\u0027s shadow fading in and out as it moves with the ship across the terrain.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vardicd","CreatedById":75832,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-22T03:03:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223491715\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179961\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542855724\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257176\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022taniwha\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, taniwha said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, this is the issue that SunFixer fixes. The issue that KSP 1.3 fixed is the ship\u0027s shadow fading in and out as it moves with the ship across the terrain.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReally that got fixed? I swear it still happens when I play. I\u0027ll have to look closer next time I play.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"taniwha","CreatedById":57176,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-22T03:06:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, ok, \u0022fixed\u0022 \u003Cspan\u003E:) (more likely improved)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"avalancha","CreatedById":143355,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-22T06:10:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223491710\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179961\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542855279\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002275832\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022vardicd\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, vardicd said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee below, though I\u0027m sure you can do a much better job showing it:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/LlhNe59KEKk?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAhaaaa now that\u0027s what I call helpful, thank you! Installing tonight after work \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vardicd","CreatedById":75832,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-22T07:57:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223491690\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179961\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542852843\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually I may need more of an explanation of what this does, because I just did a close (like less than 100 meters at orbital velocity) Minmus flyby and the shadow looked exactly the same with and without the mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: OH it\u0027s the sun moving, not the ship. Okay yeah I see that. I thought this fixed how your shadow vanished on descent or something like that \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Nope, still not seeing it. I reinstate my request. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223491710\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179961\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542855279\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002275832\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022vardicd\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, vardicd said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe this has more to do with the jerkiness of shadows moving across the ground, due to the movement of the sun in the sky. if you watch the shadows of the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E moving across the ground as the day passes in a relatively low time warp, then install this mod and watch again, you should see a big difference. See below, though I\u0027m sure you can do a much better job showing it:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/LlhNe59KEKk?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223491715\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179961\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542855724\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257176\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022taniwha\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, taniwha said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, this is the issue that SunFixer fixes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/73725-5thhorseman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002273725\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/73725-5thhorseman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@5thHorseman\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0The issue this mod affects is the movement of shadows across the ground, due to the movement of the sun [time of day] I posted a video above, relinked in this post, that shows the movement of the building shadows across the ground at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E. the first 17 seconds of video show the shadows moving in a very jerky, stop and go fashion. This is without Sunfixer. the remaining 10 seconds of video shows the same shadows moving across the ground much smoother, with Sunfixer installed. Both videos are recorded at 100x time warp. This mod doesn\u0027t actually make any changes to the Sun itself, so far as I understand it. \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-22T08:40:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223491792\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179961\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542873438\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002275832\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022vardicd\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, vardicd said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe issue this mod affects is the movement of shadows across the ground, due to the movement of the sun [time of day] I posted a video above, relinked in this post, that shows the movement of the building shadows across the ground at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E. the first 17 seconds of video show the shadows moving in a very jerky, stop and go fashion. This is without Sunfixer. the remaining 10 seconds of video shows the same shadows moving across the ground much smoother, with Sunfixer installed. Both videos are recorded at 100x time warp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah the problem was I tried it on Mun, where the sun moves much slower across the sky, so the jerkiness was hidden in the fact that the shadows weren\u0027t changing much. When I did it at the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E it was much more pronounced.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vardicd","CreatedById":75832,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-22T08:52:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223491806\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179961\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542876028\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah the problem was I tried it on Mun, where the sun moves much slower across the sky, so the jerkiness was hidden in the fact that the shadows weren\u0027t changing much. When I did it at the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E it was much more pronounced.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnderstandable, was just trying to help, and\u00A0clear up any confusion you may have had.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-22T11:49:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay the gif was ridiculously large in file size, or ridiculously small on the screen. There was no middle ground. So, I made a regular video that would fit on a 3.5\u0022 floppy if those still existed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57176-taniwha/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257176\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57176-taniwha/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@taniwha\u003C/a\u003E feel free to put this in the first post. Or not. No bigs \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/HAvox3_zFfw?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"taniwha","CreatedById":57176,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-22T14:28:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/73725-5thhorseman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002273725\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/73725-5thhorseman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@5thHorseman\u003C/a\u003E: Thank you. I\u0027ll do that after I get some sleep (been streaming for about 8 hours, a mix of KSP, blender and coding).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"taniwha","CreatedById":57176,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-24T10:45:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is with mixed feelings (though mostly pleased) that I hereby mothball SunFixer now that KSP is fixed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-27T15:39:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223527927\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179961\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548326755\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257176\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022taniwha\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/24/2019 at 2:45 AM, taniwha said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is with mixed feelings (though mostly pleased) that I hereby mothball SunFixer now that KSP is fixed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for this\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57176-taniwha/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257176\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57176-taniwha/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@taniwha\u003C/a\u003E, your work is always appreciated! Why mixed feeling though?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"taniwha","CreatedById":57176,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-28T01:04:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMixed because it\u0027s sad to see a mod fade away for any reason.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}